</div></div><div class="sqs-block horizontalrule-block sqs-block-horizontalrule" data-block-type="47" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1742561273792_89520"><div class="sqs-block-content"><hr /></div></div><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1742561273792_81727"><div class="sqs-block-content">

<div class="sqs-html-content">
  <h1 style="white-space:pre-wrap;">DRCT Appoints Interim Executive Director</h1><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">On Friday, February 7, staff and members of the DRCT Board of Directors and PAIMI Advisory Council gathered to bid farewell to our esteemed colleague and Executive Director, Deborah Dorfman. In the four years Debbie was at DRCT, she worked tirelessly and successfully on behalf of people with disabilities in Connecticut. She has left DRCT a stronger and more vibrant organization, and we will miss her.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">I am privileged to step in as the Interim Executive Director. I have served as the Deputy Executive Director for the past three years. DRCT’s mission will continue to adhere to its federal mandate and be guided by its priorities and objectives to advance and protect the civil rights of people with disabilities in Connecticut. Connecticut residents continue to experience abuse and neglect, barriers to accessing community integration, education, employment, housing, health care, and the right to participate in decision making due to ableist and deficient policies and systems. </p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">We are a small organization, but our staff is outstanding, and I am honored to be at the helm during this time of transition.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Sincerely,</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Santina Sciaba-Douglas<br>﻿Interim Executive Director<br>Disability Rights Connecticut</p>
</div>




















  
  



</div></div><div class="sqs-block button-block sqs-block-button" data-block-type="53" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1742561273792_71519"><div class="sqs-block-content">

