<div class="sqs-html-content">
  <h2 style="white-space:pre-wrap;">DRCT Receives an Award at Connecticut Valley Hospital Remembrance Ceremony!</h2><h3 style="white-space:pre-wrap;">By Mike Whilby, Strategic Partnerships Manager</h3><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">On Wednesday, May 22nd, Disability Rights Connecticut (DRCT) attended the Patient Cemetery Remembrance and Advocacy Awards Ceremony at Connecticut Valley Hospital (CVH) in Middletown. Congratulations go out to DRCT Staff Attorney, Steve Byers and Alum, Jim Welsh for receiving Certificates of Appreciation awards based on their unwavering dedication and steadfastness to patients at CVH. What an incredible honor!</p>
